<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">United
                                        States Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-06"><hi rend="italic">August 6, 1903</hi></date>.
                                (Received 12.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p>August 6, 10 a.m. Confidential. Note reference to treaty 1846 in the
                            committee report. Colombia dreads above all things newspaper reported
                            intention of the United States to denounce the treaty in the event of
                            rejecting canal treaty.</p>
                        <p>I have additional confirmation the statement of my dispatch No. 49 June
                            15.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>,</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>